## ğŸ’¡ So... What is DevOps?

> **DevOps** is the process of **developing, building, deploying, and testing on the same day** â€” which improves coordination between development and operations teams.  
>  
> We use multiple tools in the DevOps process to achieve this â€” for example:  
> **Configuration Management**, **CI/CD pipelines**, **Monitoring**, and **Automation**.

---

## ğŸ”„ Daily DevOps Cycle

1. Developer writes code today  
2. Code is **immediately** sent to testing  
3. Testing is done **same day**  
4. Bugs are fixed quickly  
5. Code is deployed to **DEV/Staging**  
6. If all good â†’ deployed to **production**

### ğŸ“… Example â€“ Day 1 Task:

> **Feature**: Signup Form  
> **Fields**: First Name, Last Name  
>  
> Testing team finds **2 defects**  
> - 1 valid  
> - 1 invalid  
>  
> Developer fixes the valid one âœ…  
> Code is deployed the **same day**

